00:08:20.800 --> 00:08:23.160
If it doesn't get to your eye, you cannot see it.

00:08:23.160 --> 00:08:25.160
So you end up with a dark star.

00:08:25.160 --> 00:08:29.200
And that was this kind of thought experiment that led to being a black hole.

00:08:29.200 --> 00:08:30.820
This dark star is actually a black hole.

00:08:30.820 --> 00:08:37.620
So even in the 1700s, you know, philosophers, you know, religious people like Reverend Mitchell thought about these ideas,

00:08:37.620 --> 00:08:40.720
about what it could look like if you had such an object.

00:08:40.720 --> 00:08:44.140
And these objects often seemed, well, this was just a thought experiment.

00:08:44.140 --> 00:08:52.920
